{"questionId":"9074994","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the acceleration of the sledge is about –2 m s<sup>–2</sup>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«friction force down slope» =&nbsp;<em>μmg</em> cos(6.5) =&nbsp;«5.9 N»</p>\n<p>«component of weight down slope» = <em>mg</em> sin(6.5)&nbsp;«=&nbsp;6.1 N»</p>\n<p>«so <em>a</em> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{F}{m}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>F</mi>\n    <mi>m</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>»&nbsp;acceleration = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{12}}{{5.5}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>5.5</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> = 2.2&nbsp;«m s<sup>–2</sup>»</p>\n<p><em>Ignore negative signs </em></p>\n<p><em>Allow use of g = 10 m s<sup>–2</sup></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074994","referenceCode":"17N.2.SL.TZ0.1e.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that the acceleration of the sledge is about –2 m s–2.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.1 – Motion","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}